Open VS Code and go the folder named Project4-starter-template-2025

Run in project folder: 
npm install

Start the Server
npm start

You should see:
ðŸš€ Server running on http://localhost:3000
ðŸ“š Students API is ready!

The API is now live at:
http://localhost:3000

ðŸ“š API Endpoints
All endpoints use the base route:

/api/students
GET â€“ Retrieve All Students
Request:
GET http://localhost:3000/api/students

Response Example:
{
  "success": true,
  "count": 6,
  "data": [
    { "id": 1, "name": "Cuthbert L", "email": "CL@email.com" },
    ...
  ]
}

POST â€“ Create a New Student
Request:
POST http://localhost:3000/api/students
Body (JSON):
{
  "name": "New Student",
  "email": "new@student.com"
}

Response:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "generated-uuid",
    "name": "New Student",
    "email": "new@student.com",
    "createdAt": "2025-02-12T..."
  }
}

GET â€“ Retrieve a Student by ID
Request:
GET http://localhost:3000/api/students/:id

Example:
GET http://localhost:3000/api/students/3
Response (if found):
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 3,
    "name": "John Thames",
    "email": "JT@email.com"
  }
}

PUT â€“ Update a Student
Request:
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/students/:id
Body (JSON):

{
  "email": "updated@student.com"
}
Response:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 3,
    "name": "John Thames",
    "email": "updated@student.com",
    "updatedAt": "2025-02-12T..."
  }
}

DELETE â€“ Remove a Student
Request:
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/students/:id
Response:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 3,
    "name": "John Thames",
    "email": "JT@email.com"
  }
}

Testing the API with Postman
-Open Postman Desktop
-Create a new request
-Select the appropriate HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
-Enter the correct URL
-For POST & PUT:
-Click Body â†’ raw â†’ JSON
-Enter JSON data
-Click Send